00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.760
Cheney & Co.

00:00:02.780 --> 00:00:06.000
Steven E. Hedley

00:00:06.020 --> 00:00:07.440
Good afternoon everyone.

00:00:07.460 --> 00:00:12.240
I'm very excited to introduce our next keynote speaker,

00:00:12.260 --> 00:00:15.440
Joe Cheng, the CTO of RStudio.

00:00:15.480 --> 00:00:18.299
And since Joe is talking about Shiny,

00:00:18.320 --> 00:00:21.420
I thought I'd introduce him with a little story, a personal story,

00:00:21.440 --> 00:00:23.240
about Shiny.

00:00:23.260 --> 00:00:24.900
And as many of you know,

00:00:24.920 --> 00:00:27.040
I wrote the book Mastering Shiny, and you might think,

00:00:27.040 --> 00:00:30.400
well, why did Hedley write that and not Joe?

00:00:30.420 --> 00:00:33.660
So Joe came to me, I don't know, like four or five years ago and said,

00:00:33.680 --> 00:00:37.200
hey, like, I want to write a book about Shiny, what should I do?

00:00:37.220 --> 00:00:39.220
And so I gave him my book writing advice,

00:00:39.240 --> 00:00:41.459
which is, writing a book's really easy.

00:00:41.480 --> 00:00:44.660
All you need to do is write for an hour a day for a year,

00:00:44.680 --> 00:00:47.619
and at the end of the year, you'll have that book.

00:00:47.639 --> 00:00:52.180
Now, as far as I know, no one has successfully followed that advice.

00:00:52.200 --> 00:00:54.599
So it's provably terrible advice.

00:00:54.639 --> 00:00:58.619
And after my advice failed for Joe for some time,

00:00:58.639 --> 00:01:01.299
I kind of took pity on him and said,

00:01:01.320 --> 00:01:04.900
oh, hey, I love writing books, like, I'll write it for you.

00:01:04.919 --> 00:01:07.419
And to kind of cut to the end of the story,

00:01:07.440 --> 00:01:11.059
I wrote Mastering Shiny, and to say thank you,

00:01:11.080 --> 00:01:13.620
Joe built me a bike,

00:01:13.639 --> 00:01:18.519
which is the most amazing bicycle that I've, like, ever ridden in my life.

00:01:18.540 --> 00:01:22.739
And it seemed to me just like this perfect example of a win-win.

00:01:22.739 --> 00:01:26.519
Like, I got all of the pleasure of writing a book,

00:01:26.540 --> 00:01:29.199
and I didn't have to build a bicycle myself,

00:01:29.220 --> 00:01:32.599
and Joe got all the pleasure of building me a bike

00:01:32.620 --> 00:01:34.160
and didn't have to write a book.

00:01:34.180 --> 00:01:36.559
So, please welcome Joe Ching.

